<sect1>
  <title>Veil2 Views</title>
  <para>
    For performance some of the views in <literal>Veil2</literal> are
    materialized.  Such views also come in a non-materialized version,
    which has the same name with a <literal>_v</literal> suffix.
  </para>
  <para>
    There are also views named with a <literal>_info</literal> suffix.
    These are intended for use by developers only.  They provide the
    same data as the non <literal>_info</literal> version of the view,
    but with bitmaps converted to arrays.  This is simply an aid to
    understanding and debugging.  Please do not use these views for
    production purposes.
  </para>
  <para>
    The following views are defined in
    <literal>veil2/sql/veil2--&version_number;.sql</literal>:
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
	<link linkend="view_all_role_roles">all_role_roles</link>;
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<link linkend="view_all_role_privileges">all_role_privileges</link>;
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<link linkend="view_accessor_contexts">accessor_contexts</link>;
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<link linkend="view_superior_scopes">superior_scopes</link>;
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<link linkend="view_all_superior_scopes">all_superior_scopes</link>;
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<link linkend="view_scope_tree">scope_tree</link>;
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<link linkend="view_promotable_privileges">promotable_privilege</link>;
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<link linkend="view_all_accessor_roles">all_accessor_roles</link>;
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<link linkend="view_role_chains">role_chains</link>;
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<link linkend="view_all_accessor_privs">all_accessor_privs</link>;
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<link linkend="view_all_session_roles">all_session_roles</link>;
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<link linkend="view_session_privileges_info">session_privileges_info</link>.
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </para>
